com.amplifyframework.datastore.storage.sqlite.adapter

Class SQLPredicate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amplifyframework.datastore.storage.sqlite.adapter.SQLPredicate

  • public final class SQLPredicate
extends java.lang.Object
    SQL Predicate adapter that adapts QueryPredicate to be compatible with SQLite use-cases. Adapted SQLPredicate object can be used to obtain query string in SQLite WHERE statement format alongside its selection arguments. For example: 
         
     QueryPredicate nameCheck = QueryField.field("name").eq("Jane");
     SQLPredicate adapted = new SQLPredicate(nameCheck);
     LOG.verbose(adapted.toString()); // Prints "name = ?"
     LOG.verbose(adapted.getSelectionArgs()); // Prints "[Jane]"

    • Method Detail

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns the SQL WHERE statement that is equivalent to the provided instance of QueryPredicate. This is a prepared statement, where "?" represent values to be replaced with variables, which can be obtained by getBindings() method. The method will return a list of strings to replace "?"s with in the same order that they appear in the query string.
